===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|chatoyant|lang=fr}}, present participle of {{term|chatoyer|lang=fr}}, from {{term|chat||cat|lang=fr}} (because of the reflective qualities of a cat's eye).

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ʃəˈtɔɪənt/|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{context|jewelry|lang=en}} Having a certain optical [[reflectance]] effect, which can be likened to the sheen of a spool of silk.

====Related terms====
* [[chatoyancy]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|mineral|lang=en}} A hard stone, such as the [[cat's-eye]], which presents on a polished surface, and in the interior, an undulating or wavy light.

